Shanghai’s Stocks Jump More Than 10% From 2011 Low, Making it Asia’s Best

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-07T07:15:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/shanghai-s-stocks-jump-more-than-10-from-2011-low-making-it-asia-s-best.html
  China ’s stocks rallied today after
the government said domestic consumption will drive economic
growth over the next five years. The benchmark index rebounded
12 percent from the low of the year in January, making it the
best performer among  Asia ’s major markets this year.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 53.90, or 1.8 percent, to
2,996.21 at the 3 p.m. close, the highest since Nov. 15. It
surged 12 percent from the 2011 low set on Jan. 25. The CSI 
300 Index advanced 2 percent to 3,334.51 today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  